le to your class. You may also find some unique skills not yet available to anyone. Some enhancements may add a title to your character based on what choices you have made in enhancing your character; these titles will be visible to other players.<br><br>In order to attain these skills, you will be able to toggle your experience into the alternative advancement pool. When you do this, your experience will be allocated to this pool in lieu of your “leveling” experience bar. Once a certain amount of experience has entered the alternative advancement pool, you will receive training points that may be allocated to acquiring your enhancements. When you acquire the proper amount of training points, you will have the option of choosing which enhancement you wish to gain, although some enhancements may have pre-requisites that will need to be obtained before you are able to acquire it.<br><br>Players will have the option of toggling between the normal experience pool to gain levels, or back to the alternative enhancement pool to gain enhancements whenever they wish (although this may require you to zone after you have toggled your switch). Switching between the two pools will not cause you to lose experience in the other. Experience loss due to death suffered by the character will be taken from the “Leveling” experience pool, it will not impact your alternative advancement pool. <br><br>The alternative advancement system will allow for a variety of enhancements to choose from for each class. Those who chose to enhance their character with this system may find a higher level of individuality in their character.<br><br><br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>Unknown/Miscellaneous<br>Acrobatics - This ability will reduce the damage taken from falling.<br><br>Physical Enhancement - This ability will give the player additional improvement in thier Natural Durability, Avoidance Boost, and Mitigation Boost abilities.<br><br>Body and Mind Rejuvenation - This ability will give the player 1 additional point of mana and hitpoint regeneration.<br><br>Strong Root - This ability will give the player a lure save root.<br><br>Mass Group Buff - This ability will turn your next group buff into an beneficial area effect spell. Hitting everyone within its radius.<br><br>Spell Casting Fury 2 - This ability gives the player an increased percent chance to critical with direct damage spells.<br><br>Extended Buff - This ability increases the duration of beneficial buffs by an additional 20 percent.<br><br><br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>Warrior<br>Bandage Wound - This ability will give the player increased healing capabilities through bandage by 10, 25, and 50 percent.<br><br>Warcry - This ability will allow the player to give their entire group immunity to fear for a period of time based on skill level.<br><br>Area Taunt - This ability will allow for the player to taunt everything in a small radius.<br><br>Rampage - This ability will allow for the player to attack everything in a small radius.<br><br>Flurry - This ability will allow for the player to have up to 2 additional attacks off of their primary hand.<br><br><br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>Rogue<br>Purge Poison - This ability will remove all poison affects from the player.<br><br>Purifying Tonic<br>Removing 4 Poison counters<br>Removing 4 Poison counters<br>Removing 4 Disease counters<br>Removing 4 Disease counters<br><br>Quick Throw - This ability will allow the player to have additional throwing attacks on one throw.<br><br>Throwing Mastery - This ability will give an increased chance to critical by 5, 15, and 30 percent.<br><br>Double Riposte - This ability will give the player an increase chance to execute a double riposte 10, 20, and 30 percent of the time.<br><br>Poison